# Stack Rules — Expo Router + Supabase

## Routing
- Use Expo Router file-based routing.
- Role routes live in route groups: `(player)`, `(scout)`, `(club)`, `(org)`.

## Supabase
- Use one Supabase client module; do not create multiple clients.
- Store media in Supabase Storage buckets:
  - `avatars`
  - `videos`

## Data access
- Prefer server-authoritative data (Supabase) over heavy local state.
- Keep RLS in mind: only participants can access messages; users can edit only their own profile/content.

## Minimalism
- Avoid introducing complex state libraries unless already in repo.
- Prefer straightforward patterns that are easy to maintain by agents.
